<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Aerospace on My New Hugo Site</title><link>https://example.org/categories/aerospace/</link><description>Recent content in Aerospace on My New Hugo Site</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 01 Jun 2025 10:00:00 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://example.org/categories/aerospace/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>TEST: Spacecraft Research and Open Source Simulation</title><link>https://example.org/researches/test-spacecraft-research/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Jun 2025 10:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://example.org/researches/test-spacecraft-research/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>This is a test research report for the Researches section. The topic is spacecraft simulation and open source tools for aerospace engineering.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="project-overview">Project Overview&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>We explore the use of open source software to simulate spacecraft attitude control and orbital mechanics.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="key-features">Key Features&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Real-time 3D visualization&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Physics-based simulation&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Modular codebase&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="example-code">Example Code&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Here is a simple Python example for simulating a spacecraft&amp;rsquo;s attitude using quaternions:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">import&lt;/span> numpy &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">as&lt;/span> np
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">from&lt;/span> scipy.spatial.transform &lt;span style="color:#f92672">import&lt;/span> Rotation &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">as&lt;/span> R
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># Initial attitude (quaternion)&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>q0 &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> R&lt;span style="color:#f92672">.&lt;/span>from_euler(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#39;xyz&amp;#39;&lt;/span>, [&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff">0&lt;/span>, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff">0&lt;/span>, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff">0&lt;/span>], degrees&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">True&lt;/span>)&lt;span style="color:#f92672">.&lt;/span>as_quat()
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># Simulate a rotation about the Z axis&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>delta_q &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> R&lt;span style="color:#f92672">.&lt;/span>from_euler(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#39;z&amp;#39;&lt;/span>, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff">45&lt;/span>, degrees&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">True&lt;/span>)&lt;span style="color:#f92672">.&lt;/span>as_quat()
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># New attitude&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>q1 &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> R&lt;span style="color:#f92672">.&lt;/span>from_quat(q0) &lt;span style="color:#f92672">*&lt;/span> R&lt;span style="color:#f92672">.&lt;/span>from_quat(delta_q)
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;New attitude (quaternion):&amp;#34;&lt;/span>, q1&lt;span style="color:#f92672">.&lt;/span>as_quat())
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="open-source-project">Open Source Project&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>We use the &lt;a href="https://www.orekit.org/">Orekit&lt;/a> library for orbital mechanics and the &lt;a href="https://github.com/spacecraft-sim/spacecraft-simulator">Spacecraft-Simulator&lt;/a> project for real-time visualization.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>